0is%20not%20only%20awarded%20for%20artistic%20work%20but%20also%20for%20international%20understanding%20and%2C%20in%20your%20case%2C%20your%20commitment%20to%20freedom%20in%20the%20world.%20What%20does%20this%20prize%20mean%20to%20you%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20very%20important.%20I%20think%20all%20of%20us%20in%20the%20world%20of%20books%20are%20familiar%20with%20this%20prize.%20And%20a%20remarkable%20list%20of%20people%20have%20it.%20So%20I%E2%80%99m%20just%20very%20gratified%20to%20have%20my%20name%20added%20to%20that%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHow%20are%20you%20today%2C%20only%2014%20months%20after%20you%20were%20attacked%20and%20seriously%20injured%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fsalman-rushdie%2Ft-39350490%5C%22%3ESalman%20Rushdie%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20As%20you%20see%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20feeling%20much%20recovered.%20I%20mean%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20a%20little%20beaten%20up%2C%20but%20I%E2%80%99m%20alright.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20New%20Yorker%3Cem%3E%C2%A0in%20February%2C%20you%20said%20that%20you%20have%20been%20suffering%20from%20writer%E2%80%99s%20block%20since%20the%20attack.%20But%20a%20few%20days%20ago%2C%20your%20publisher%20announced%20that%20you%20will%20be%20publishing%20a%20new%20book%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%5B%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EKnife%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9C%5D%C2%A0%3Cem%3Enext%20spring%2C%20in%20which%20you%20deal%20with%20the%20attack%20and%20its%20consequences%20for%20you.%20How%20did%20you%20find%20your%20way%20back%20to%20writing%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20just%20came%20back.%20I%20think%20quite%20soon%20after%20I%20spoke%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20Yorker%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%20that%20interview%2C%20I%20found%20that%20it%20began%20to%20flow%20again.%20So%20I%E2%80%99m%20happy%20that%20I%E2%80%99ve%20been%20able%20to%20write%20this%20book%2C%20which%20will%20come%20out%20in%20the%20spring.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWas%20there%20anything%20that%20helped%20you%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYou%20know%2C%20just%20practice.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20been%20doing%20this%20job%20a%20long%20time.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20gets%20you%20back%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20talk%20about%20your%20current%20book%2C%20%E2%80%9CVictory%20City%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20was%20published%20this%20year.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20fictionalised%20telling%20of%20the%20rise%20and%20fall%20of%20the%20medieval%20city%20of%20Bisnaga%20in%20southern%20India%2C%20where%20men%20and%20women%20of%20diverse%20faiths%20were%20meant%20to%20be%20equal.%20But%20the%20empire%20perishes%20at%20the%20end%20because%20it%20abandons%20all%20its%20ideals.%20Is%20this%20a%20commentary%20on%20the%20contemporary%20world%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20mean%2C%20if%20you%20write%20about%20history%2C%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20also%20writing%20about%20the%20present%20day%20because%20when%20we%20look%20at%20the%20past%2C%20we%20see%20what%20interests%20us%2C%20our%20own%20concerns%20reflected%20in%20earlier%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20really%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20world%20of%20my%20own.%20There%20are%20many%20writers%20who%20have%20done%20this%2C%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20William%20Faulkner%20with%20his%20Yoknapatawpha%2C%20%5BGabriel%5D%20Garcia%20Marquez%20with%20Macondo%2C%20or%20the%20Indian%20writer%20R.%20K.%20Narayan%20with%20Malgudi.%20I%20wanted%20a%20little%20world%20of%20my%20own%2C%20and%20this%20saga%20became%20that%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESome%20critics%20have%20said%20that%20the%20book%20is%20a%20feminist%20novel.%20Was%20that%20your%20intention%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20one%20of%20the%20things%20that%20interested%20me%20doing%20the%20research%20for%20the%20book%20was%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20really%20true%20that%20in%20this%20very%20long%20ago%20period%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0this%20is%20the%2014th%20and%2015th%20century%20we%E2%80%99re%20talking%20about%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20the%20place%20of%20women%20in%20society%20was%20very%20advanced%20in%20many%20ways.%20There%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20given%20to%20the%20education%20of%20girls%2C%20with%20almost%20as%20many%20schools%20for%20girls%20as%20for%20boys.%20Women%20worked%20in%20every%20walk%20of%20life%3A%20in%20the%20army%2C%20in%20the%20legal%20profession%2C%20or%20as%20merchant%20traders%2C%20et%20cetera.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20true%2C%20but%20of%20course%2C%20the%20thing%20about%20history%20is%20that%20nothing%20is%20true%20all%20the%20time.%20And%20my%20character%20Pampa%20Kampana%2C%20who%E2%80%99s%20in%20a%20way%20telling%20the%20story%20that%20I%E2%80%99m%20retelling%2C%20her%20own%20life%20goes%20up%20and%20down%2C%20there%20are%20moments%20when%20she%E2%80%99s%20queen%2C%20and%20there%20are%20moments%20when%20she%E2%80%99s%20an%20exile%20in%20the%20jungle.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20also%20true%20of%20the%20values%20of%20the%20society.%20There%20are%20moments%20when%20it%E2%80%99s%20liberal%2C%20tolerant%20and%20open%2C%20and%20other%20moments%20when%20it%20becomes%20illiberal%20and%20intolerant.%20I%20guess%20human%20life%20is%20like%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20fatwa%20imposed%20on%20you%20over%2034%20years%20ago%20almost%20cost%20you%20your%20life%20during%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20attack.%20Why%20are%20autocrats%2C%20dictatorships%C2%A0and%20powerful%20people%20so%20afraid%20of%20stories%20of%20literature%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20always%20been%20the%20case%2C%20you%20know%2C%20in%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20world%C2%A0that%20dictators%20fear%20poets.%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20strange%20because%20writers%20have%20no%20armies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20your%20explanation%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20think%20they%20fear%20alternative%20versions%20of%20the%20world.%20One%20of%20the%20things%20about%20authoritarian%20rule%20is%20it%20also%20imposes%20its%20own%20version%20of%20the%20world%20to%20the%20exclusion%20of%20all%20others.%20Of%20course%2C%20all%20writers%20have%20their%20own%20version%20of%20the%20world%20and%20sometimes%20those%20don%E2%80%99t%20please%20people%20in%20power%2C%20and%20so%20they%20try%C2%A0to%20silence%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAmid%20the%20current%20war%20between%20Hamas%20and%20Israel%2C%20what%20can%20literature%20do%20to%20help%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVery%20little.%20You%20know%2C%20I%C2%A0always%20try%C2%A0not%20to%20overstate%20the%20power%20of%20literature.%20What%20writers%20can%20do%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20and%20what%C2%A0they%20are%20doing%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20to%20try%20and%20articulate%20the%20incredible%20pain%20that%20many%20people%20are%20feeling%20right%20now%20and%20to%20bring%20that%20to%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20attention.%20I%20think%20writers%20everywhere%20are%20doing%20that%20right%20now%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20probably%20the%20best%20we%20can%20do%3A%20articulate%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESo%C2%A0are%20you%20saying%20that%C2%A0words%20in%20this%20situation%20lose%20their%20power%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20just%20think%20there%20are%20things%20that%20words%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%2C%20and%20what%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20is%20stop%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20casualties%20usually%20of%20war%20is%20truth%20because%20people%20start%20presenting%20their%20own%20propaganda%20version%C2%A0of%20events.%C2%A0And%20that%E2%80%99s%20very%20difficult%20when%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20distinguish%20fact%20from%20fiction%20in%20a%20war%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20think%20the%20problem%20reporters%20and%20journalists%20have%20to%20face%20now%C2%A0is%20how%20to%20establish%20the%20facts.%20And%C2%A0if%20journalism%20can%20do%20that%2C%20then%20it%E2%80%99s%20performing%20a%20very