er%20members%20of%20the%20public%20in%20the%20immediate%20aftermath%2C%20chastising%20and%20singling%20out%20Starbucks%E2%80%94not%20Defendants%E2%80%94for%20supporting%20Hamas%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20Workers%20United%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.courthousenews.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Fworkers-united-v-starbucks-complaint.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecountersued%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20chain%20in%20federal%20court%20in%20Pennsylvania%2C%20asking%20to%20be%20allowed%20to%20continue%20to%20use%20the%20circular%20green%20Starbucks%20Workers%20United%20logo.%20The%20union%20also%20denied%20supporting%20violence.%20%26quot%3BStarbucks%20Workers%20United%20did%20not%20make%20a%20%26quot%3Bstatement%26quot%3B%20let%20alone%20multiple%20%26quot%3Bstatements%26quot%3B%20advocating%20for%20violence%2C%20nor%20did%20the%20union%20take%20a%20%26quot%3Bposition%26quot%3B%20supporting%20violence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20union%20said%20Starbucks%20apparently%20referenced%20an%20unauthorized%20post%20on%20the%20union's%20X%20account%20that%20was%20deleted%20after%2030-40%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20union%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20referred%20Insider%20to%20an%20October%2017%20message%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstories.starbucks.com%2Fpress%2F2023%2Fstarbucks-condemns-acts-of-terror-strongly-disagrees-with-statements-made-by-workers-united%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20the%20company's%20chief%20partner%20officer%2C%20Sara%20Kelly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20message%20says%2C%20in%20part%3A%20%26quot%3BStarbucks%20unequivocally%20condemns%20acts%20of%20terrorism%2C%20hate%20and%20violence%2C%20and%20we%20strongly%20disagree%20with%20the%20views%20expressed%20by%20Workers%20United%2C%20including%20its%20local%20affiliates%2C%20union%20organizers%20and%20thos